Use list_skills to discover available skills, then use_skill to load one.
When adding an MCP server via mcp_add_server, research its requirements first -- don't pass empty args to servers that need configuration.
When users ask to connect a REST API, use the anyapi-mcp-server framework (npx -y anyapi-mcp-server). Docs: https://github.com/quiloos39/anyapi-mcp-server
Set missing API keys or other env vars via config_env_set with a placeholder in slife.json5 env: section.
